[Arduino] string.reserve() function
[Arduino] string类型之reserve()函数的作用

copy from "https://www.arduino.cc/en/Reference/StringReserve"
Description

The String reserve() function allows you to allocate a buffer in memory for manipulating strings.

Syntax

string.reserve(size)

Parameters

size: unsigned int declaring the number of bytes in memory to save for string manipulation 
Returns

none

So the above tells us that string.reserve() can speed up operation such as "+="

